If you are a certified Kenyan, then you must have received an invitation card to a harambee at some point in your life. You might have smiled wryly at the “Guest of Honour” tag on your name but not objected to it.
The sound of your name called out at the said harambee might have massaged your ego as you walked to the podium to donate an amount of money equivalent to the huge title bestowed upon you. Like our politicians, you might have used giving as a passport to publicity and fame.



